{meta: title Stand By Me}
{meta: artist Ernest Tubb}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]When the storms of life are raging [F]stand by [C]me
When the storms of life are raging stand by [G7]me
When the world [C]is tossing me like a ship upon the [F]sea
Thou who [C]rulest wind and [G7]water stand by [C]me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
When the midst of tribulation [F]stand by [C]me 
When the midst of tribulation stand by [G7]me
When the hosts [C]of hell assail and my strength begins to [F]fail
Thou who [C]never lost a [G7]battle stand by [C]me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
When the midst of faults and failures [F]stand by [C]me
When the midst of faults and failures stand by [G7]me
When I do [C]the best I can and my friends [F]misunderstand
Thou who [C]knowest all [G7]about me stand by [C]me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
When I'm growing old and feeble [F]stand by [C]me
When I'm growing old and feeble stand by [G7]me
When my life [C]becomes a burden and I'm nearing chilly [F]Jordan
O Thou [C]Lily of the [G7]Valley stand by [C]me  
{end_of_verse}
